    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-03-16T21:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-03-16T21:30:00-05:00" n="92"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d92">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                    Indonesia/3–1748</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Batavia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Livengood</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Batavia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-03-17T10:00:00+07:30"
                            >March 17, 1948—10 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2114. <gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 183. Report sent to President
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d92fn1">For text of telegram dated March 16 by <gloss
                            target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss>, see <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, <hi
                            rend="italic">3rd yr., Suppl</hi>. (Jan.–March), p. 37, doc.
                        S/697.</note> (<gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 182<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d92fn2">Telegram 213, March 17, from Batavia, not printed; it quoted
                        the text.</note>) was drafted by DuBois on basis working papers submitted by
                        <gloss target="#t_NethDel1">NethDel</gloss> and accepted by <gloss
                        target="#t_IndoDel1">IndoDel</gloss> at meeting steering committee March 16.
                    Intention is that report be circulated to <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>
                    members for their information only.</p>
                <p>Encountered initial opposition from Critchley to sending report this nature since
                    he presumably would prefer not to waste <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC’s</gloss>
                    ammunition by sending non-controversial material. We hope, however, that by
                    sending report this character at this time, it will not be necessary to send a
                    further report on political discussions until agreement has been reached or
                    unless there is a breakdown in discussions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Livengood</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
